OL,3,CBlackpool rock 'under severe threat'
OL,4,Cfrom imported imitations
OL,6,FDavid Thorp, who penned the letter,
OL,7,Fsays companies can't compete with the
OL,8,FChinese imports, which are sold to
OL,9,Fwholesalers at 3p per stick cheaper
OL,10,Fthan theirs. This undercutting will
OL,11,Fsee "at least two" more factories in
OL,12,FBlackpool close down in the next year,
OL,13,Fhe fears.JMr Thorp, who runs Stanton
OL,14,Fand Novelty Confectioners, said: "It's
OL,15,FChinese rock that's really poor
OL,16,Fquality but it's cheaper than we can
OL,17,Fsell it for.
